// Console's own primary database (Prisma 7, multi-file schema).
//
// This is the FIRST proving instance of the platform-services pattern
// (see `.agents/rules/platform-services.md`): an app/service owns its own
// bounded-context datastore and references core 876 identity entities by
// OPAQUE ID only — never by a cross-database foreign key. Identity details
// (name, email, avatar, org slug) are resolved at read time through the
// `$876` client surface, not joined here.
//
// What lives here: admin-console-internal state only (MC users/access grants,
// MC roles, notes, settings). What does NOT: identity/platform data (the real
// user/org records,
// memberships, org-roles, features, audit_events, vendors/customers/locations)
// — those stay in the 876 identity API and are reached through `$876`.
//
// Multi-file: this file holds the generator + datasource; each model lives in
// its own sibling `*.prisma` file in this folder. The schema folder is wired in
// `prisma.config.ts` (`schema: "prisma/schema"`).

generator client {
  provider = "prisma-client"
  output   = "../../src/lib/db/generated/prisma"
}

datasource db {
  provider = "postgresql"
}
